Zoom Node Deployments - Command Injection Vulnerability
Column1:
1/21 CH - Monitor for QID | Discuss Watchlist 

CVE-2026-22844 is a critical command injection vulnerability in Zoom Node Multimedia Routers (MMRs) affecting versions prior to 5.2.1716.0. A meeting participant with network access and low privileges may be able to inject arbitrary commands, leading to remote code execution on the MMR, potentially compromising confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the system and connected infrastructure.

As of the latest published information, no public proof-of-concept (PoC) exploit has been widely reported yet, and there are no confirmed in-the-wild exploitation reports. However, the combination of low attack complexity and minimal privilege requirements suggests that exploitation could be relatively straightforward once details or exploit code become public, so applying the vendor patch is urgent.
